{{Youmay|a [[Slicer/Legends|slicer]] in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity|[[Baylan Skoll]], the [[Dark side adept|dark side]] [[mercenary]] in the new [[canon]]}}
'''Baylan''' was something of a minor legend among [[Slicer/Legends|slicing]] circles, famed for his skill at infiltrating and fixing computer systems. His reputation suggested he had done this mainly through the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]], and that he could overcome 2048-bit encryption.<ref name="AR">{{LivingForce|Eye of the Sun: Revelation and Refutation}}</ref> In [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]], [[Gerta Haman]] was able to call in some favors to get Baylan to program a [[Datapad/Legends|datapad]] with impressive decryption software, capable of slicing almost any system while disguising the activities as routine memory checks.<ref name="AR" />

==Behind the scenes==
Those who played ''[[Eye of the Sun: Revelation and Refutation|A Revelation]]'' at the convention where it premiered were able to keep Baylan's datapad for their characters after the event. It granted gargantuan bonuses to rolls made to infiltrate systems, but would only function four more times.<ref name="AR" /> The gamemaster notes in the adventure ''[[Clouds of Genarius: Into the Storm Clouds|Into the Storm Clouds]]'' mention that this item could be used to bypass the computer security of the weapon of mass destruction ''[[Conkesta]]''.

